# official information:
https://helm.sh/

helm chart is a technic to deploy your docker image built to a cluster (aka K8S cluster)

Helm Chart can be a seprate folder where it defines application information eg: docker image and ingress (aka domain name) or 
Helm Chart can be included in application folder

Basic step to generate Helm Chart on Linux:
# add helm and check helm version
bash
module add helm

helm version

# To create a helm-chart folder
cd templates
helm template .

# Then modify files to include docker image, ingress (DMS), etc then test it out by trying to deploy

# additional useful commands
helm list -n <name space>
helm uninstall <app/db name> -n <name space>

# install db
helm install <app/db name> -<db type> <file>.tar \
  --set global.xyz \
  ...
  -n <name space> # must include a name space

helm rollback ...

helm install --atomic ... # deploy must run susceessfully otherwise eg: error then automatically rollback (fully clean as not yet deployed)

